{"lemma":"هِيْل","slug":"هِيْل","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n44399"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%84"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of هَالَ (hāla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"piled sand"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pile, to dump","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cardamom"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ه ي ل (h y l) in the sense of “pouring” and “pile”, as the Arab custom is to place cardamom pods in coffee, pouring it through the pods that pile up at the spout of a coffee pot.\n\nEtymology tree\nProto-South Dravidian *ēlV-der.\nSouth Dravidianbor.\nSanskrit एला (elā)bor.\nClassical Persian هیل (hēl)bor.\nArabic هيل\nBorrowed from Classical Persian هیل (hēl), borrowed from Sanskrit एला (elā), borrowed from a South Dravidian language, from Proto-South Dravidian *ēlV- (“cardamom”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44399","headword_ar":"هَيْلٌ","root":"hyl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAla","text_ar":"هَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HavaA","text_ar":"حَثَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayolN","text_ar":"هَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAy^ilN","text_ar":"هَايِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"Sand"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that will not remain steady in its place, but falls down."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}